    <section class="guide-takeaways">
      <h2>Key Takeaways</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Valuation multiples are derived from real closed transactions - they reflect what buyers actually paid, not asking prices</li>
        <li>Multiples vary significantly by industry: car washes at 4.99×, HVAC at 3.17×, restaurants at 2.15×</li>
        <li>Recurring revenue, low owner involvement, and diverse customers drive multiples toward the upper quartile</li>
        <li>The best-to-worst adjustment swing is over 1.3× - equal to $390,000+ on a $300,000 SDE business at a 3.0× median</li>
        <li>Use the industry-specific multiple range, not a generic "2–4×" range, for any meaningful planning</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

